name: 李老师不是你老师
content:
In early January, Cao Kui, a chemistry teacher from a well-known middle school in Beijing, told the Economic Observer that he was confused by an abnormal phenomenon in a required experiment in high school chemistry. The experiment involved a well-known drug, enteric-coated aspirin tablets. Since the brand of enteric-coated aspirin tablets used in the experiment was changed two years ago, the experimental results have been visible to the naked eye.
According to him, the enteric-coated aspirin tablets detection experiment is a required experiment in the second-year chemistry class. The purpose is to detect the carboxyl and ester groups in acetylsalicylic acid, the active ingredient of aspirin. In the ester group test, acetylsalicylic acid needs to be hydrolyzed first, and salicylic acid will be produced after hydrolysis. When salicylic acid encounters ferric chloride, a color change reaction occurs, and the solution appears purple.
Now, since the solution changes color before and after the hydrolysis experiment, this link has lost its meaning, and the above phenomenon is common, and the results of student operations and teacher operations are consistent.

To reenergize officials paralyzed by fear of anti-corruption purge, Xi: Some mistakes are acceptable.
Wall Street Journal: Xi Jinping is stepping up his anti-corruption drive, a fight that has resulted in record numbers of officials being disciplined, with the side effect of many officials being afraid to act for fear of punishment.
To help officials reenergize and revive a stagnant economy, Xi also delivered a message: Some mistakes are acceptable. His instructions to the Communist Party: Enforcing strict discipline should not foster an atmosphere of timidity that would undermine the enterprising spirit that once drove China's economic rise.
Xi said there should be a "combination of strict management and kindness" to "motivate cadres to forge ahead and do things."
